{ \mon } At the { \moff } Fa -- ther’s com -- mand, the shoes and the ring.

}

wordsD = \lyricmode {
\set stanza = "4."

{ \mon } And the { \moff } ver -- y best robe, and the fat -- ling, and wine,
{ \mon } (What a { \moff } change from the rags, and the husks, and the swine!)
